laboratory_examinations.findings: Dilated contrast-filled loops of small bowel measuring at least 4.7 cm. In the region of the appendix, there is an 8-mm appendicolith and free fluid with small locules of air suggestive of a perforated appendicitis. Discontinuity of the appendiceal wall and mild dilation of colonic loops measuring 4.1 cm. No evidence for obstruction.
Serum creatinine level is 2.5 mg/dL (ref range 2.7-4.5 mg/dL), indicating low creatinine.
